< Text>
I received a $1 off a regular sub coupon so I called in and asked if it could be applied to a wrap. The male associate was very rude and told me no. So I go to place an order for a regular sub online. Right after, I notice the coupon didn't apply. So I immediately called in and got the same associate. I asked him to cancel the order and see if he could issue a refund. He told me he'd cancel it but wouldn't and couldn't give a refund. I asked for a manager, he replied one wasn't in.

I asked what I should do. He told me I'd have to contact Subway directly because he already hit confirm. I couldn't believe I'd have to waste so much time because he wouldn't help me in any way. I also know full well he was lying about not being able to issue a refund on an item I didn't receive and was never even made in the first place.

This is the worst Subway franchise I've ever been to.< /Text>

Carney's is located on the Sunset Strip in a train car. Parking is easy and the service is fast and friendly.

Don't go with fancy here. They have great hot dogs and hamburgers. Stick with those items and you will be in heaven. They have a wonderful selection of hot dogs and will make you a burger anyway you want it.

You can dine in or take out. We love dinning in. Sometimes there is a wait, but it is not usually too bad. You will like this place. Super tourist and kid friendly. Have a great time.</review>

<userid>112828455244746111861<//userid>< name>
Alizen< /name>
< date>
1556186303910< /date>
<rating>4<//rating>< Review>
I always get excited when I hear about poke joints in YL, but this one didn't live up to the hype for me.

I came here because it was relatively new and I wanted to try it out. I'm a huge fan of poke bowls, and what really sets different poke restaurants apart from each other really comes down to the toppings that are included with the price you pay and the level of service you receive.

* PRICE / PORTION *
A regular bowl is $8.95 and a large bowl is $11.75. Regular is 3 scoops of fish vs a large which is 5. I wouldn't recommend getting the large unless you're really hungry or you're splitting it with somebody else.

* TOPPINGS *
I really like that they give generous portions for each topping, especially the seaweed salad which I have always had to pay for (it's free here)! I'm slightly disappointed that their avocado topping has gone from being free to an additional charge of $0.49. I also think it's strange how they have a huge amount of day-old avocado in a quarter pan when they should have just preserved the freshness of the avocado with some lemons. It looks more appealing that way, in my opinion.

The house sauce is alright. I believe it's a mixture of soy sauce and peanut oil, which doesn't really send me. Not much of a kick to it but not much flavor other than the peanut either. The sauce truly makes it or breaks it for me, so I would recommend trying out a different sauce than their house special.

* SERVICE *
The employees are NICE, but nice really doesn't cut it for me. I was very disappointed to see that one of the food service workers had so many strands of hair sticking outside of her ponytail and hat. I thought the purpose of wearing a hat was to keep hair away from the food, so why isn't anyone there to tell her to redo her ponytail? Speaking of anyone there, where was the manager on duty? Or the assistant manager? Or a supervisor? I checked in on Yelp to receive my free miso soup and neither the FSW nor the cashier had any idea about the promotion. Instead, the cashier decided to call his manager on the phone to verify the promotion rather than just honoring it. Cmon, the miso soup was only $1. I'm not so much disappointed in not getting the miso soup as I am about there not being any authoritative figure there at all.

I hope that they can make improvements with the quality of their service and the presentation of their food/toppings. Maybe then will I return to this location for a second chance.<//Review>

<review>My standards for gyms are fairly low. I've been to a few 24 Hour Fitness Super Sport gyms, and this is one of the better ones. I don't shower here, I don't swim here, I don't do personal training--I go for solo lift-based workouts and as soon as I'm finished, I'm out the door. It's clean (or as clean as it could be--unfortunately most gym goers I've observed don't wipe machines after themselves, which is gross). The layout is one of the better ones and it doesn't feel cramped. Be wary that peak times start early and end late. Even at 6am, I'm waiting 15 min for an Olympic rack.

As far as robberies go, I always bring everything with me around the gym in my bag. It's kind of obnoxious, but as long as it's out of the way, it's a far better alternative to having your locker broken into.<//review><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Resp>None</Resp>< gmapID>

< Review>
I've been attending this gym for close to a year.  Yes the place is new and for the most part the facilities are clean.  Some of the equipment (including in the locker rooms) is malfunctioning or unusable and they take a while to fix things.  Sometimes the fixes are just a bandaid and the equipment will go down again in short order.  Despite the facility being large, it can be quite crowded.  I have to echo some of the other reviewers on the professionalism of the staff.  Many of the staff leave something to be desired, though, to be fair, a select few of them are nice.  The other gym members are also concerning.  On more than one occasion I have found people who don't know proper etiquette when using the gym and the aggression on display is disturbing.  I would have to say that I am looking for an alternative at this point.  A gym should be a comfortable atmosphere for working out in a timely fashion.  This gym falls short on this goal and I would suggest considering alternatives.</Review>

<text>(07/06/19)
Downgrading my review further to 1 star. I'd give them 1/2 if I could. Staff is indifferent, you better watch your back there since if anything is stolen from you, not only can they do nothing about it (that's a given, we all know that petty theft is tolerated even by law enforcement), they will act like  it and even more so, they dismiss you like a pest (basically pouring salt on your wound with their indifference).  Decent gym and equipment but not the safest and certainly not the friendliest.  I rarely go here anymore and largely split my time between the Arquez Location (the BEST staff) and the Mountain View Location (safer).

Also I agree with many others that the standard of cleanliness at high traffic times (7-9pm) just isn't there. Bathrooms are straight disgusting. They need to have the staffing doing their self proclaimed "Team Cleans" more often.... I hear them announce it on the intercom but I don't see it being done with much vigor or enthusiasm.  All goes back to customer service: the staff TOP-BOTTOM seem like they'd rather be anywhere else but there.  I echo many folks' sentiments here regarding the management here.  They don't manage, and they don't care.

One final point about removing the towel service: everybody knows it's not for the environment since someone has to wash the towels - and clean people who go to a dirty gym will wash them after 1X use - so the towel washing will continue and it will harm the environment and consume the resources of mother earth  just the same, only difference now is that the COST will be PASSED ON to the customer.  The marketing people could have at least made their reasoning seem less ridiculous and more sincere in their print ads by encouraging members not to wash towels at home after at least two uses!

< Text>
Did a three day pass there. Parking is difficult. Expect a pre workout just to get to the door.  I went to swim. The pool already had  two to three to a lane all three days all the way to 10 pm. I saw the same at Citi Sports as well.  Lots of retired people in the area enjoying their lifetime rates. I couldn't get a good swim in, either the circle was too.slow or not even moving as the swimmers convert to water walking. And I am not a fast swimmer. The hot tub was always filled with old ladies lifting their cell phone above the water to not get them wet as their speak Mandarin over the speaker phone.  I  not sure how each lady did not disturb the other as they were not being shy about their voice.   Maybe they were talking to each other.   It is a shared sex hot tub.  The locker room was sletchy and crowded. You will be within arms reach of another whenever you are in the locker room.  The guys did seem considerate and quiet. The place is really crowded during the busy times in the evening. I mean really crowded.  The 24 hour Active on Arques is less crowded for the machines.    There are machines stacked everywhere, hallways, everywhere.  There are also a bunch of rv  dwellers using the club to get in their daily showers  late at night. They park on the streets around the club. I am ok with that.  There is no serenity in this club.  I am still without a club, I am not donating to 24 hour chain even with the Costco deal.< /Text>

<name>Translation Linguistics</name><userid>108272873803498736619< /userid><pics>None</pics>< review>
Multiple issues with this location, even as a paying member:

1. Bathrooms frequently have urine/water/bits of trash all scattered about them.

2. Dust all over the gym floor (even in big clumps, especially near the squat racks).

3. Staff has a 'whatever, sort it out yourself' attitude when approached with issues. That, or they find reasons to hide in the back of the staff section to not have to deal with it.

4. Broken treadmills upstairs remain unfixed.

5. No Air Conditioning upstairs so you get fatigued/hot rather quickly.

6. Bent deadlift/benchpress bars + too few resistance bands.

7. No enough lockers in locker area.

Do not recommend.</review>

<userid>117302909570148222669</userid><Name>Robert Finley< /Name><Date>1451705698798<//Date>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Review>
I've used about a dozen different 24hr fitness facilities from San Diego to Seattle, including what I was told was the largest and heaviest attendance facilities in California (LA/Riverside area.)

Sunnyvale exceeds my hopes and expectations.

This facility should be studied by all chain gyms, including other 24hr fitness and area managers in the 24hr fitness chain.

You will notice the cardio area is on the second floor (mezzanine).  If you recognize this as a flaw, popular with LA fitness chains, don't despair.   These guys make it work.  A common flaw with 24hr fit gyms is front desk employees (and district managers) want the 24hr fitness official music channel to be this loud oppressive inescapable part of the gym experience, so they can enjoy their personal taste in music while spamming you with advertisements every five minutes, (remind you of FM radio?  How's that industry doing?)

This gym is better than that.

Cardio is on the second floor because this facility is full of equipment.  No space is wasted.  Their music doesn't drown out your music.

Sweat and be miserable.  But, do it while enjoying your own personal music.

Your personal trainer won't need to shout to be heard in your session.

Your ears won't be bleeding after a workout from trying to drown out the PA system.

It is worth fighting traffic for this gym over all others in my area.</Review>

<user>109510494362706135522< /user><Name>Dr. Gagandeep Singh</Name><date>1317708113286</date><rating>1< /rating>< Text>
I recently relocated to Sunnyvale and was looking out for a gym with a swimming pool..thats it. When I went to the club, I repeated what I was looking for thrice. Instead, the so called advisor kept on insisting that I join this club at a whopping $65 a month. I told him I did not need so many fancy facilities and he then started justifying the cost as the area was expensive, rents were high etc. NEVER DID HE TELL ME that there was a 24 hour fitness with exactly what I wanted just half-a-mile away @$35/month. He ignored my comments on what I wanted and comments that this place was too, too expensive. Infact, I even told him I used to go to a community club in Chicago suburbs that charged $41.5 a month, but gave best quality towels, complementary digital day-lockers, complimentary high quality shampoo, conditioner, body wash and moisturizing lotion in each bathroom. The place had a huge lap-pool and well maintained free and fixed weights sections....but as usual, this guy never listened to me.

When I complained via the 24-hour fitness website, I got a follow up call and the girl on the phone said that the guy must have been totally occupied with his thoughts. I told the girl I kept on insisting the price was too high and that I did not need so many facilities, yet the "advisor" never listened to me & didn't guide me appropriately. She then gave me a lame excuses justifying his actions.
Not only do these people suck at their behavior, but they so dumb they cannot even make good excuses! What a pity! A pack of completely useless people with poor ethics.

The club people boast they provide towels - however the towels in the club are thin rags, no good. a total 24-hour rip-off!
DO NOT GO THERE! Look around, you will find clubs from $19-35 a month depending on the facilities you want....< /Text>

< review>
I've been going to this 24h location since it opened - probably 7+ years ago. I workout 6 days a week, in the very early morning (5-6am), which means I have never had problems with crowding. I focus mostly on strength training, and have not made use of the pool, group classes, or cardio equipment.

Generally speaking, this location is very well maintained and has a very wide  selection of equipment. The introduction last year (2015) of their 8-station CrossFit rig  has greatly expanded the areas where you can squat and deadlift. When things break, they get fixed in reasonable amounts of time.

For my HIIT workouts, I use the Schwinn spin cycles and their Concept2 rowing machines. Again, because I am there in the early morning hours, I can always find an open machine when I need it.<//review>

< review>
Horrible place, stay away. I came in with printed out 3-day free trial pass wanting to try the gym. What I've seen was a rude, nasty, unprofessional female employee--who looked like she never worked out in her life and spoke as she never graduated from high school--acting hateful, negative, paranoid, tried to disrespect and humiliate me...for simply coming in with a trial pass I printed from their website! From the first moment, her manner of speaking was condescending, arrogant, bouncer-like--she was trying to talk like a wannabe cop--tried to deny me trial pass because I lived in Mountain View, not Sunnyvale!--so for her I was not "local"....yes, 15 minute drive away "not local"! They should fire her if they want to keep any customers. I'm publishing an article about this experience next week. <Review>Came here with the gilt city deal to try it. I defiantly think it's worth it.

We ordered a bottle of white white, they didn't have my first choice which was fine, picked another one

You basically get two glasses of sparkling wine, 2 starters, 2 entrees and dessert
FROM A LIST, not the entire menu.

Service was awful, somehow the server had a colossal attitude, after She asked me how the pasta was, which she highly recommended, and I basically answered that it was awful and we couldn't eat it and that's how it started.

The starters were good but not like, I must order these next time I come, it was simple Mediterranean dips and fritters

Sorry for telling you the truth? Not sorry?
I didn't complain and say I didn't want to pay or wanted another entree, I simple answered her question truthfully
Egg, Parmesan foam? Truffle? And Serrano hay???

The salmon on the other hand was Amazing! I would highly recommend it. I don't know about the liquid sauce you pour over the fish, but the dish made sense. I found out what the sauce is its "sorrel sauce" good talk lol. Still don't know lol

The pasta was cold, the foam and all the aspects of the pasta were just wrong and too much. The dish just doesn't make sense, I think. Remember it's my experience, not everyone's.

The desserts suck, but whatever it's a good deal and like I said a good price for trying a "fancy" spot.

After realizing she was completely rude to me, she brought out another dessert "ON HER", to which I said no thank you, if my friend wants it.

Thanks but no thanks

I'm sure you will have a better experience but that's mine.
The first time I ate here was way better.<//Review><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPBuMmIVH9GzR11hYIueGhpEvWrjNC8yvBwgcNg=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN60n7QaL66IMtfJSBCh9JGmedB-QTX0XLnca17=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics>< response>

<user_name>Ryan Silver< /user_name>< Time>
1566847641636< /Time>
<Rating>1</Rating>< review>
Food at this restaurant is delish , however if you have any food allergies be super careful here. My daughter has Celiacs disease which is a severe gluten allergy, we explained this to our waiter who assured us her meal would be gluten free and it wasn't because she a severe reaction after eating here.  Their gluten free menu is a joke ( its looks just like the regular menu with a sticky note that says gluten free on it) and they obviously don't take food allergies serious, based on the way they handled our complaint after the fact. They gave us such runaround to speak to all these different managers and then didn't even follow back up with us and return our calls.  We are providing you this feedback so no one else should ever be sick from your restaurant.<//review>

< text>
I have been here a number of times now and I must say that the restaurant is very consistent.

High quality food and drinks with one of the coolest interior designs in the city.

Just recently went to tea for Mother's Day and was not disappointed.

A mix of classic foods that are occasionally reconstructed to create never before tasted delicacies.

The price is the only deterrent, but well worth the experience in my opinion.

Another side note, the Bazaar next door ( by the same chef ) is a bit more stylized in regards to the food and d√©cor.< /text>

<Text>We had Thanksgiving dinner at Tres and liked the experience - did not love it! Both food and service were ok. The atmosphere was nice - make sure specially request a table by the fireplace. That looked very cosy :)

The food was nice but the menu not very inventive. The turkey was a bit dry and would have needed a bit more sauce.

They rather quickly bought the bill (without us asking for it) and we settled it, but ended up talking and sitting at the table for quite a while longer - it felt a bit weird that they never came around to check with us if we wanted any more water/ wine/ eg. Also the courses came in a bit rushed - we had not finished the starters before they brought out the next course.

Smallish things like that took the starts down form 4/5 to just 3 and it ended up being just an OK experience!</Text>< pics>

My storage unit along with some dozen others was burglarized sometime between Aug. 22 and Aug. 24.  In fact management said it happened over a period of two days before they contacted me. Further insult to injury just this morning they notified me they're increasing my rent after just a few months. Leo Paskin<//Name>
<date>1411364851022< /date><rate>5</rate>< Review>
My wife and I had to store about a 2-bedroom apartment 's worth of stuff, so we went on the hunt for a storage location.  The Public Storage on Capitol Expwy popped up as one of the closer locations, and had very good reviews everywhere we looked.  When we went to go check out this location and other places, this was our first stop and our last.  The facility is great!! Mike and Nahid are super friendly and keep this place in great shape!  We couldn't be happier with our storage unit. We paid a fair price for it and all with no hassle.

It is now a week later and all of our stuff is moved in.  We're in an indoor space, and out of all of the days we've been there (which have been the hottest we've had in the area for the past few weeks), the temperature inside was surprisingly cool.  This was a big surprise to us and really sealed the deal on this location.

If you need some storage space, come check this one out, Mike and Nahid will help you get what you need!  We can't thanks them enough!< /Review>

<username>Paige Torey<//username><Pics>None</Pics><UserId.>106103726068298127907<//UserId.><resp>None< /resp>< text>
This location is lazy, unprofessional, and doesn‚Äôt give a care about customer service.
I had ordered a dishwasher for my ill grandmother since her dishwasher had been broken for a long time. This was on Sunday the 27th. I was able to schedule an appointment for delivery and installation for October 30th.
Well, the 30th arrived and I get a phone call from the installer, Anthony, stating that he had gone to the store and they didn‚Äôt have the dishwasher yet. Looking online, it had showed the appointment was for 8am to 12pm, when in reality, the appointment was actually set for 12pm to 4pm. Anthony said he saw that on his end too, so we could wait a little bit and he would check back with me.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY to try to find out where my order was. After a little bit of digging and calling around, I was assured by a lady over the phone that my order was on the truck and ready for delivery and installation; That the ETA was 2:30pm.
About 2pm, I get a call from Anthony that he was at the store a second time to check on where this dishwasher was. It still was not at the store. He told me that the store was supposed to have called me the night before to let me know so that we weren‚Äôt just waiting around all day for an order that was never going to arrive. I never received such a phone call. I let Anthony know that the lady over the phone told me that the delivery and installation was supposed to be in about a half hour, and that everything looked fine on her end.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY again to figure out what the heck was going on.
I got help from a wonderful lady named Sammi, who was able to dig around even more and even contacted Anthony directly as well. They together figured out that the San Jose (Plant location) made a mistake by not contacting me the night before, nor did they contact me the day of. There was absolutely no communication.
Sammi explained to me that when Anthony spoke to the manager, they said that my order was in a different city and they had to fill out a form, which was supposed to have been done the day before when they were supposed to call me anyway. So it‚Äôs just more of the whole people not doing their damn job.
Sammi said that I shouldn‚Äôt have been able to schedule delivery and installation so soon, that it was supposed to black out certain days.
The only apology I got was from Sammi, who did absolutely nothing wrong. She was actually the one that helped me reschedule for a later date for delivery and installation to make certain we will get our dishwasher.
I am extremely unhappy. I made a trip out of state to California to be here with my grandmother and get a few things done to lighten the load on her. She is very sick and all of this is going to put more stress on her. I am only here for a few days.
I don‚Äôt understand why my order isn‚Äôt here when it was supposed to be or what exactly happened in general because I never got direct answers. I‚Äôm not sure what city the dishwasher is in currently or why.
I feel like someone didn‚Äôt do their job and I‚Äôm the one paying for it.
Avoid this place at all costs.</text>

Well, the 30th arrived and I get a phone call from the installer, Anthony, stating that he had gone to the store and they didn‚Äôt have the dishwasher yet. Looking online, it had showed the appointment was for 8am to 12pm, when in reality, the appointment was actually set for 12pm to 4pm. Anthony said he saw that on his end too, so we could wait a little bit and he would check back with me.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY to try to find out where my order was. After a little bit of digging and calling around, I was assured by a lady over the phone that my order was on the truck and ready for delivery and installation; That the ETA was 2:30pm.
About 2pm, I get a call from Anthony that he was at the store a second time to check on where this dishwasher was. It still was not at the store. He told me that the store was supposed to have called me the night before to let me know so that we weren‚Äôt just waiting around all day for an order that was never going to arrive. I never received such a phone call. I let Anthony know that the lady over the phone told me that the delivery and installation was supposed to be in about a half hour, and that everything looked fine on her end.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY again to figure out what the heck was going on.
I got help from a wonderful lady named Sammi, who was able to dig around even more and even contacted Anthony directly as well. They together figured out that the San Jose (Plant location) made a mistake by not contacting me the night before, nor did they contact me the day of. There was absolutely no communication.
Sammi explained to me that when Anthony spoke to the manager, they said that my order was in a different city and they had to fill out a form, which was supposed to have been done the day before when they were supposed to call me anyway. So it‚Äôs just more of the whole people not doing their damn job.
Sammi said that I shouldn‚Äôt have been able to schedule delivery and installation so soon, that it was supposed to black out certain days.
The only apology I got was from Sammi, who did absolutely nothing wrong. She was actually the one that helped me reschedule for a later date for delivery and installation to make certain we will get our dishwasher.
I am extremely unhappy. I made a trip out of state to California to be here with my grandmother and get a few things done to lighten the load on her. She is very sick and all of this is going to put more stress on her. I am only here for a few days.
I don‚Äôt understand why my order isn‚Äôt here when it was supposed to be or what exactly happened in general because I never got direct answers. I‚Äôm not sure what city the dishwasher is in currently or why.
I feel like someone didn‚Äôt do their job and I‚Äôm the one paying for it.
Avoid this place at all costs.<//Review>

<Rating>1< /Rating><Review>I decided to use the best buy 18 months interest free financing to purchase about $4200 worth of appliances on november 6th. Delivery was scheduled for november 9th.
I  called back the next day to change the delivery address (forgot to say I am moving from an apartment to my new house), they said since i changed the address the delivery window was no longer available (both addresses about 2.5 miles apart) and would have to be rescheduled.

Rescheduled for the following week between 8-12pm. no one showed up, driver calls to say "oh i have 12-4". I said no, was already on my way to go empty out old apartment, so had to toss all my frozen stuff.
went to best buy, cancelled the transaction and gave them back the free google chrome.
Someone called Angie called and I agreed to get re-delivery on the 24th.
delivery went smooth, no issues. all is well, then I get an  email from best buy credit card (CITI) today and they say "you missed  the first payment on december 2nd so you are charged a late fee" I went ape nuts.

I  dont have a bill yet, how can I be late, I had even written a letter to them saying my purchase date was changed to the 24th not the 6th. they say they only go by the order date, irrespective of wether you actually receive the items.  I refused to pay the late fee, paid the balance off and closed the account.
The one star is for their staff (they were all great) and the products (love my whirlpool washer, dryer and samsung fridge, also got a dyson vaccum cleaner and iphone x).  the entire experience was tedious and stressfull, I had been thinking of making best buy my go-to place for stuff but i think ill stick with amazon.< /Review>< Pics>

<Text>Location is a bit hidden in the Mcarthy Ranch area. Being near by the waste business at 237 freeway, I usually walk quick to get into the store because the air reeks really bad and when I would finish shopping, I would rush to my car for the same reason. The place is sometimes dead but, that means usually their products are in stock then. Save yourself some time, call to check if what ever item you want is in stock before driving up there. The service is great, sucks that they can't really help you with credit card issues like increasing the limit, they only can sign you up for it. Citi Bank is the credit issuer towards their store credit card so, look out for that. <UserId.>103136226799416260286</UserId.><user_name>Ryan Sampson< /user_name><time>1472077893752< /time><Rating>5< /Rating><text>Long story long I arrived on bad terms and left on good terms. After coming to the understanding that the warranty for my problem was up to the manufacturer Lenovo and not a liability of Best Buy, the Geek Squad associate Kevin politely informed me that anything that could be done to fix the problem immediately would be over his head, as the problem was with a workstation urgency was present. In steps the General Manager Kellie Adams.

She laid out what Best Buy policies are and being an understanding person I accepted that I bought a low-end computer and we got what we paid for. What she did say was that she would do whatever was in her power to make sure that I walked out that door happy.

The positive attitude of Kevin and Kellie turned me from being someone that did not plan on ever coming back to Best Buy to someone who walked out the door with a purchase of two new workstations. I have a growing company and I know where I will be going for hardware from now on.

It's easy to find the motivation to write a bad review, it takes a lot for me to find it worth my time to write a positive one. If management is reading this take notes.< /text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Response>None< /Response><gmapID>0x808e3316b820b6ed:0x4161ce5586427bfb<//gmapID></record>
